.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH k2i-maintenance-compact 1  "k2i-maintenance-compact "
.SH NAME
k2i\-maintenance\-compact \- Run compaction
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBk2i\-maintenance\-compact\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run compaction
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH EXTRA
BEHAVIOR:
  Scans the configured table for files smaller than compaction_threshold_mb,
  groups them toward compaction_target_mb, writes replacement Parquet files,
  and commits the resulting metadata through the configured catalog path.
